organization.description: The National Institute for Applied Statistics Research Australia (NIASRA) is a research institute based at the University of Wollongong, Australia. It aims to identify Australia as a place where the discipline of applied statistics collaborates with academics and professionals in science, government, business and industry to tackle strategic problems. More information on NIASRA can be found at http://niasra.uow.edu.au/what-is-niasra/index.html

name: melanoma-skin-cancer-incidence
notes:
Description
---------------

This data was taken from the R `lattice' package. The data is described in the package as follows:

These data from the Connecticut Tumor Registry present age-adjusted numbers of melanoma skin-cancer incidences per 100,000 people in Connectict for the years from 1936 to 1972. 

Format
------------

A csv file has 37 observations on the following 2 variables.

- year: years 1936 to 1972.

- incidence: rate of melanoma cancer per 100,000 population.

References
--------------
Ramsay, James O., and Silverman, Bernard W. (2006), Functional Data Analysis, 2nd ed., Springer, New York.
title: Melanoma Skin Cancer Incidence
